The paper discusses the use of blockchain technology in securing Electronic Health Records (EHRs) and enabling patients to control their own health data, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and healthcare (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the adaptation of blockchain mechanisms into m-Health applications, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes conceptual solutions for future blockchain implementations, which involves cryptography (cs.CY).
